$ Registry: HKEY_CURRENT_USER

`HKEY_CURRENT_USER` (HKCU) manages settings for the currently logged-in user.

Technically, `HKCU` is a link to a subkey of `HKEY_USERS`.

On Windows NT systems, the settings for each user are stored in the files â†’ Windows/dirs/Users/username/NTUSER_DAT[`%USERPROFILE%\NTUSER.DAT`] and `USRCLASS.DAT`.
